By Vincent Ikuomola, Abuja  There is no going back on the planned sanitation of the social media space, the Federal Government insisted on Thursday. Minister of Information and Culture Lai Mohammed stated this in Abuja during an audience with online publishers. He declared no amount of criticism will deter the government from going ahead with the proposed measure. He insisted it was the right thing to do as Nigeria was not alone in this regard. Details shortlyâ€¦